1/*
2* CreateCaseRedirectControllerMVN
3* Created By: Roman Lerman
4* Created Date: Jan 1, 2013
5* Description: This class creates a new interaction whenever the "New" button is clicked on the Case list view
6*/
7public with sharing class CreateCaseRedirectControllerMVN {
8    public Case newCase { get; set; }
9    public String accountId { get; set; }
10
11    public CreateCaseRedirectControllerMVN (ApexPages.StandardController controller) {
12        Case c = (Case)controller.getRecord();
13        if(ApexPages.currentPage().getParameters().get('def_account_id') != null)
14            accountId = ApexPages.currentPage().getParameters().get('def_account_id');
15    }
16  
17    public void getRedirect () {
18        newCase = new Case();
19        if(accountId != null){
20           newCase.AccountId = accountId;
21           newCase.ContactId = [select PersonContactId from Account where Id = :accountId].PersonContactId;
22        }
23        try{
24            insert newCase;
25        }catch(Exception e){
26            ApexPages.addMessages(e);
27        }
28    }
29}

CUST_RecordTypeIdLookup.cls

(100% covered)

Show Coverage
1/** 
2* @author Sean Harrison 
3* 
4* This class is called from a trigger on the CST_App_Settings_CUST__c obj. On insert or update
5* the object is checked for changes to fields containing record type api names. These names are 
6* then used to lookup the corresponding record type ids for that org and written to a companion
7* field on the same obj.
8*/
9public with sharing class CUST_RecordTypeIdLookup implements GLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface {
10    
11    public void handle() {
12        if (Trigger.isInsert || Trigger.isUpdate ) {
13            execute(Trigger.new);
14           }
15    }
16
17    void execute(List<Sobject> sobjects) {
18        List<CST_App_Settings_CUST__c> settings = (List<CST_App_Settings_CUST__c>)sobjects;
19        List<CST_App_Settings_CUST__c> settingsToProcess = new List<CST_App_Settings_CUST__c>();
20
21
22        // If any of the two fields change, refresh the ids
23        for (CST_App_Settings_CUST__c sets : settings) {
24            if (Trigger.isInsert) {
25                if (sets.Record_Types_CUST__c != null || sets.Employee_Record_Type_CUST__c != null || sets.HCO_Record_Types_CUST__c != null)
26                    settingsToProcess.add(sets);
27            } else if (Trigger.isUpdate) {
28                if ((String)Trigger.oldMap.get(sets.Id).get('Record_Types_CUST__c') != sets.Record_Types_CUST__c
29                    || (String)Trigger.oldMap.get(sets.Id).get('Employee_Record_Type_CUST__c') != sets.Employee_Record_Type_CUST__c 
30                    || (String)Trigger.oldMap.get(sets.Id).get('HCO_Record_Types_CUST__c') != sets.HCO_Record_Types_CUST__c) 
31                {
32                    settingsToProcess.add(sets);
33                }
34            }
35        }        
36                
37        // Get all Account RT info for this org
38        Map<String, Id> rtDevNameToIds = new Map<String, Id>();
39        for (RecordType rt : [select Id, DeveloperName from RecordType where SobjectType = 'Account']) {
40            rtDevNameToIds.put(rt.DeveloperName, rt.Id);
41        }
42        
43        // match the names to the ids.  
44        for (CST_App_Settings_CUST__c cst : settingsToProcess) {
45            String errorMsg ='';
46            Set<String> rtIds = new Set<String>();
47
48            // start with Employee...
49            String desiredRecordTypes = (cst.Employee_Record_Type_CUST__c != null) ? cst.Employee_Record_Type_CUST__c : '';
50            for (String s : desiredRecordTypes.split(',')) {
51                if (s.trim()!='') {
52                    if (rtDevNameToIds.containsKey(s.trim())) {
53                        rtIds.add(rtDevNameToIds.get(s.trim()));
54                    } else {
55                        errorMsg += (s.trim()+'_not_found ');
56                    }
57                }
58            }
59            String strOfRTIds = '';
60            for (String s : rtIds) strOfRTIds += s + ',';
61            if (strOfRTIds.endsWith(',')) strOfRTIds = strOfRTIds.substring(0,strOfRTIds.length()-1);
62            
63            if (errorMsg != '') {
64                cst.Employee_Record_Type_CUST__c.addError(errorMsg);
65            } else {
66                cst.Employee_Record_Type_Id_CUST__c = strOfRTIds;
67            }
68
69            // ...now do HCO...
70            errorMsg ='';
71            rtIds = new Set<String>();
72            desiredRecordTypes = (cst.HCO_Record_Types_CUST__c != null) ? cst.HCO_Record_Types_CUST__c : '';
73            for (String s : desiredRecordTypes.split(',')) {
74                if (s.trim()!='') {
75                    if (rtDevNameToIds.containsKey(s.trim())) {
76                        rtIds.add(rtDevNameToIds.get(s.trim()));
77                    } else {
78                        errorMsg += (s.trim()+'_not_found ');
79                    }
80                }
81            }
82            strOfRTIds = '';
83            for (String s : rtIds) strOfRTIds += s + ',';
84            if (strOfRTIds.endsWith(',')) strOfRTIds = strOfRTIds.substring(0,strOfRTIds.length()-1);
85            
86            if (errorMsg != '') {
87                cst.HCO_Record_Types_CUST__c.addError(errorMsg);
88            } else {
89                cst.HCO_Record_Type_Ids_CUST__c = strOfRTIds;
90            }
91
92            // ...finish up with default list.
93            errorMsg ='';
94            rtIds = new Set<String>();
95            desiredRecordTypes = (cst.Record_Types_CUST__c != null) ? cst.Record_Types_CUST__c : '';
96            for (String s : cst.Record_Types_CUST__c.split(',')) {
97                if (s.trim()!='') {
98                    if (rtDevNameToIds.containsKey(s.trim())) {
99                        rtIds.add(rtDevNameToIds.get(s.trim()));
100                    } else {
101                        errorMsg += (s.trim()+'_not_found ');
102                    }
103                }
104            }
105            strOfRTIds = '';
106            for (String s : rtIds) strOfRTIds += s + ',';
107            if (strOfRTIds.endsWith(',')) strOfRTIds = strOfRTIds.substring(0,strOfRTIds.length()-1);
108            
109            if (errorMsg != '') {
110                cst.Record_Types_CUST__c.addError(errorMsg);
111            } else {
112                cst.Record_Type_Ids_CUST__c = strOfRTIds;
113            }
114        }
115    }    
116}

1/**

4 * Base controller that builds an edit page layout dynamically via the Metadata API

6 */
7
8public virtual with sharing class GLBL_BaseEditController {

26            ));

35        
36        //set record type

40        } else if(FieldssObject.contains('recordtypeid') && mySObject != null) {
41            sObjectRecordType = (String)mySObject.get('recordtypeid');

53    public class PageBlockSection {
54        public List<Field> fields { get; set; }
55        public String title { get; set; }
56        public Integer columns { get; set; }

72    public List<PageBlockSection> sections {

74            system.debug('getting sections!');

78                PageBlockSection pBs;

81                sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.Soap handler = HandlerMetadataInit();
82

84                sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.DescribeLayoutResult LayoutResult = handler.describeLayout(this.sObjectAPIName, new list<String>{sObjectRecordType});
85
86                if (LayoutResult != null) {
87                    //we take the first one because we queried only one recordtype.

102                                   //System.debug('LAYOUT ITEM ---> '+layoutItem);

107                                              //The user shouldn't change the OwnerId/RecordType this way.

110                                              f.readOnly = true;
111                                              f.value = layoutComponent.value;
112                                              pBs.fields.add(f);
113                                          }
114                                          else if (layoutitem.editable == false && layoutComponent.value != null) {
115                                            f = new Field();
116                                            f.id = layoutComponent.value;
117                                            f.readOnly = true;
118                                            f.value = layoutComponent.value;
119                                            pBs.fields.add(f);
120                                        }
121                                          else if (layoutComponent.value != null) {
122                                              f = new Field();
123                                              f.id = layoutComponent.value;
124                                              f.readOnly = false;
125                                              f.value = layoutComponent.value;

128                                        }

130                                }

132                                    f = new Field();
133                                    f.blankspace = true;
134                                    pBs.fields.add(f);
135                                }
136                               
137                            }
138                        }
139                        pBs.index = sections.size();
140                        sections.add(pBs);
141                    }
142                }
143            }

145        }

151    public static sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.Soap handlerMetadataInit() {
152        //here the authentication to the soap partner.
153        //we build something quite dynamic which does not depend on any url (like cs17.salesforce.com)
154        //therefore, should work for production like for sandbox, however the remote site settings
155        //needs to be updated in Salesforce in Order to allow this outbound communication.
156
157        sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.Soap handler = new sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.Soap();
158
159        handler.endpoint_x = 'https://' + System.URL.getSalesforceBaseURL().getHost().split('\\.')[1]  + '-api.salesforce.com/services/Soap/u/27.0/' + UserInfo.getOrganizationId();
160        
161        sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.SessionHeader_element sessionHeader = new sobjectPartnerSoapSforceCom.SessionHeader_element();
162        sessionHeader.sessionId = UserInfo.getSessionId();
163        handler.SessionHeader = sessionHeader;
164        return handler; 
165    }

78    public virtual PageReference remove() {
79        List<GenericSobjectWrapper> newChildList = new List<GenericSobjectWrapper>();
80        List<Sobject> childrenToDelete = new List<Sobject>();
81        List<GenericSobjectWrapper> childrenList;

84        } else {

86        }

92                childrenToDelete.add(sow.so);

94        }

96        if (recordTypeDeveloperNameParam != null) {
97            childrenMap.put(recordTypeDeveloperNameParam, newChildList);
98        } else {
99            children = newChildList;
100        }
101        return null;
102    }

112            } else {

119                    childrenToUpdate.add(sow.so);

123                }
124            }

133                return null;
134            } else {
135                return new PageReference('/'+parentId);
136            }
137        } catch (Exception e) {

139            return null;
140        }

228    public virtual class GenericSobjectWrapper implements Comparable {
229        public Sobject so { get; set; }
230        public String hash { get; set; }
231        public Integer index { get; set; }

233        public GenericSobjectWrapper(String objectAPIName) {
234            InitializeGenericSobjectWrapper(objectAPIName, null, null);
235        }
236        public GenericSobjectWrapper(String objectAPIName, ID recordTypeId) {            
237            InitializeGenericSobjectWrapper(objectAPIName, recordTypeId, null);
238        }
239        public GenericSobjectWrapper(String objectAPIName, Sobject so) {            
240            InitializeGenericSobjectWrapper(objectAPIName, null, so);
241        }
242        public GenericSobjectWrapper(Sobject genericObject) {
243            this.so = genericObject;
244            this.hash = MERC_Util.generateRandomString(10);
245        }
246        private void InitializeGenericSobjectWrapper(String objectAPIName, ID recordTypeId, Sobject so){
247            Schema.SObjectType objType = Schema.getGlobalDescribe().get(objectAPIName);
248            if (so != null) {
249                this.so = so;
250            } else if (recordTypeId != null){
251                this.so = objType.newSobject(recordTypeId, true);
252            } else {
253                this.so = objType.newSobject();                
254            }
255            this.hash = MERC_Util.generateRandomString(10);
256        }
257        public Integer compareTo(Object compareTo) {
258            GenericSobjectWrapper item = (GenericSobjectWrapper) compareTo;
259            if (index == item.index) return 0;
260            if (index > item.index) return 1;
261            return -1;        
262        }
263    }

1/** 
2* @author Sean Harrison 
3* 
4* This class is currently called from a trigger on the CST_User_Log_CUST__c obj but may be used
5* with any Sobject. On insert or update an object is checked for changes to a field containing 
6* a Lilly Global Employee Id. This id is then used to lookup a corresponding Account record 
7* and used to populate a desired lookup.
8*
9*/
10public with sharing class GLBL_GlobalIdAccountLookup implements GLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface {
11
12    private String globalIdFieldName;
13    private String employeeLKFieldName;
14    private Boolean throwException;
15
16   /**
17    * Constructor that sets the Global Id and the target lookup field as well as a Boolean
18    * determining if, when an GUIDs is invalid, whether the logic will fail silently (with
19    * debug message) or throw an exception.
20    * 
21    * @param guidField    the api name of the field containing the Global Id. E.g. GUID__c
22    * @param empField     the api name of the Account lookup field to populate as a result
23    *                    of this logic.
24    * @param throwEx     set to true to cause an exception to be thrown when the processed
25    *                    Global Id is invalid
26    */
27    public GLBL_GlobalIdAccountLookup(String guidField, String empField, Boolean throwEx) {
28        this.globalIdFieldName = guidField;
29        this.employeeLKFieldName = empField;
30        this.throwException = throwEx;
31    }
32
33   /**
34    * Constructor that sets the Global Id and the target lookup field. This instantiation 
35    * will fail silently with a debug message when an invalid GUID is encountered.
36    * 
37    * @param guidField    the api name of the field containing the Global Id. E.g. GUID__c
38    * @param empField     the api name of the Account lookup field to populate as a result
39    *                    of this logic.
40    */
41    public GLBL_GlobalIdAccountLookup(String guidField, String empField) {
42        this(guidField,empField,false);
43    }
44
45    // Sets the handler to respond to both inserts and updates with same execute method
46    public void handle() {
47        if (Trigger.isInsert || Trigger.isUpdate ) {
48            execute(Trigger.new);
49        }
50    }
51
52   /**
53    * On insert or update an object is checked for changes to a field containing 
54    * a Lilly Global Employee Id. These qualifying objects are passed to 
55    * findAndPopulateLookup() for processing
56    *
57    * @param sobjects    the List of objects upon which this trigger should operate.
58    */
59    private void execute(List<Sobject> sobjects) 
60    {
61        List<Sobject> sobjsToProcess = new List<Sobject>();
62        for (Sobject obj : sobjects) {
63            if (Trigger.isInsert) {
64                if (obj.get(globalIdFieldName) != null) {
65                    sobjsToProcess.add(obj);
66                }
67            } else if (Trigger.isUpdate) {
68                if ((String)Trigger.oldMap.get((Id) obj.get('Id')).get(globalIdFieldName) != obj.get(globalIdFieldName))
69                {
70                    sobjsToProcess.add(obj);
71                }
72            }
73        }
74
75        findAndPopulateLookup(sobjsToProcess);
76    }
77
78   /**
79    * Taking a List of Sobjects which contain a Global Id field. This id is then used 
80    * to lookup a corresponding Account record and populate a desired lookup.
81    *
82    * @param sobjects    the List of objects to process.
83    */
84    public void findAndPopulateLookup(List<Sobject> sobjsToProcess)
85    {
86        Set<String> globalIdsToProcess = new Set<String>();
87        for (Sobject obj : sobjsToProcess) {
88            globalIdsToProcess.add((String) obj.get(globalIdFieldName));
89        }
90
91        Map<String, Id> globalIdsToAccountId = new Map<String, Id>();
92        for (Account a : [select Id, Prsnl_Nbr_GLBL__c from Account where Prsnl_Nbr_GLBL__c in :globalIdsToProcess]) 
93        {
94            globalIdsToAccountId.put(a.Prsnl_Nbr_GLBL__c,a.Id);
95        }
96
97        for (Sobject obj : sobjsToProcess) 
98        {
99            if (obj.get(globalIdFieldName) != null && globalIdsToAccountId.containsKey((String) obj.get(globalIdFieldName)))
100            {
101                obj.put(employeeLKFieldName, globalIdsToAccountId.get((String) obj.get(globalIdFieldName)));
102            } else {
103                if (throwException) throw new GLBL_GlobalIdAccountLookupException('Invalid Global Id: '+obj.get(globalIdFieldName));
104                System.debug(System.LoggingLevel.ERROR, 'Invalid Global Id: '+obj.get(globalIdFieldName));
105            }        
106        }
107    }
108

110    public class GLBL_GlobalIdAccountLookupException extends Exception {}
111
112}

27/**
28 * Serializes and Deserializes SObject records and related child and referenced records using the Apex JSON support
29 *
30 *   See https://github.com/afawcett/apex-sobjectdataloader for known issues, restrictions and TODO's
31 *
32 **/
33public with sharing class GLBL_SobjectDataLoader 
34{
35    /**
36     * Configuration uses a Fluent method design (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluent_interface), 
37     **/
38    public class SerializeConfig
39    {
40        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followRelationships;
41        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followChildRelationships;
42        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followMasterRelationships;
43        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> omitFields;
44        
45        public SerializeConfig()
46        {    
47            followRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
48            followChildRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
49            followMasterRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
50            omitFields = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();             
51        }
52        
53        /**
54         * Provide a field that represents the lookup relationship the serializer should follow
55         **/
56        public SerializeConfig follow(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
57        {
58            followRelationships.add(relationshipField);
59            return this;
60        }
61
62        /**
63         * Provide a field that represents the lookup relationship the serializer should follow
64         **/
65        public SerializeConfig followMaster(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
66        {

68            return this;
69        }
70        
71        /**
72         * Provide a field that represents a parent child relationship the serializer should follow
73         **/
74        public SerializeConfig followChild(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
75        {
76            followChildRelationships.add(relationshipField);
77            return this;
78        }
79        
80        /**
81         * Provide a field that the serializer should omit from the serialized output
82         **/
83        public SerializeConfig omit(Schema.SObjectField omitField)
84        {
85            omitFields.add(omitField);
86            if(followRelationships.contains(omitField))
87                followRelationships.remove(omitField);
88            if(followChildRelationships.contains(omitField))
89                followChildRelationships.remove(omitField);
90            return this;
91        }
92        
93        /** 
94         * Automatically configure (removes all previous configuration)
95         *  Skip known system lookup and child relationships but include the rest (direct children only) upto certain depth, 
96         *  Caller can always add or omit specific via follow or omit methods
97         **/
98        public SerializeConfig auto(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType)
99        {
100            followRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
101            followChildRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
102            omitFields = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
103            Set<Schema.SObjectType> searched = new Set<Schema.SObjectType>();
104            searchRelationships(sObjectType, 0, 0, true, searched);    
105            return this;    
106        }
107        
108        /**
109         * Seek out recursively relationships
110         **/
111        private void searchRelationships(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, Integer lookupDepth, Integer childDepth, Boolean searchChildren, Set<Schema.SObjectType> searched)
112        {        
113            // Stop infinite recursion    
114            if(searched.contains(sObjectType) || lookupDepth > 2 || childDepth > 3) // TODO: Make max depth configurable
115                return;
116            searched.add(sObjectType);
117            Schema.DescribeSObjectResult sObjectDescribe = sObjectType.getDescribe();
118                        
119            // Following children? (only set for descendents of the top level object)
120            if(searchChildren)
121            {
122                List<Schema.ChildRelationship> childRelationships = sObjectDescribe.getChildRelationships();
123                for(Schema.ChildRelationship childRelationship : childRelationships)
124                {
125                    // Determine which child relationships to automatically follow
126                    String childRelationshipName = childRelationship.getRelationshipName();
127                    if(childRelationshipName==null || 
128                       childRelationshipWhitelist.contains(childRelationshipName)) // Skip relationships without names and those whitelisted
129                        continue;
130                    if(childRelationshipName.endsWith('Histories')) // Skip relationships ending in Histories (TODO: consider a RegEx approach?)
131                        continue;
132                    if(!childRelationship.isCascadeDelete()) // Skip relationships for none owned records (aka only follow master-detail relationships)
133                        continue;
134                    followChild(childRelationship.getField()).
135                        searchRelationships(childRelationship.getChildSObject(), lookupDepth, childDepth+1, true, searched);
136                }
137            }
138                            
139            // Follow lookup relationships to long as they have not previously been added as child references and are not whitelisted
140            Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectDescribe.fields.getMap();
141            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFields.values())
142                if(sObjectField.getDescribe().getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference) 
143                    if(!followChildRelationships.contains(sObjectField) && !relationshipWhitelist.contains(sObjectField.getDescribe().getName()))
144                        follow(sObjectField).
145                            searchRelationships(sObjectField.getDescribe().getReferenceTo()[0], lookupDepth+1, childDepth, false, searched);
146        }
147
148        // Standard fields that are not included when using the auto config
149        private Set<String> relationshipWhitelist = 
150            new Set<String>
151                { 'OwnerId',
152                  'CreatedById',
153                  'LastModifiedById',
154                  'RecordTypeId',
155                  'PersonContactId'
156                };
157                
158        // Standard child relationships that are not included when using the auto config
159        private Set<String> childRelationshipWhitelist = 
160            new Set<String> 
161                { 'Shares', 
162                  'ProcessInstances', 
163                  'ProcessSteps', 
164                  'Tasks', 
165                  'ActivityHistories', 
166                  'Attachments', 
167                  'FeedSubscriptionsForEntity', 
168                  'Events', 
169                  'Notes', 
170                  'NotesAndAttachments', 
171                  'OpenActivities', 
172                  'Histories', 
173                  'Feeds',
174                  'PersonEmailStatuses',
175                  'OpenActivities',
176                  'PersonOpenActivities'};    
177    }

179    
180    /**
181     * Serialize the given records using the default configuration (see SerializeConfig.auto)
182     **/
183    public static String serialize(Set<Id> ids)
184    {
185        // Serialize based on no prior knowledge of the objects
186        if(ids==null || ids.size()==0)
187            throw new SerializerException('List of Ids cannot be null or empty.');
188        return serialize(ids, new SerializeConfig().auto(new List<Id>(ids)[0].getSObjectType()));
189    }
190    
191    /**
192     * Serialize the given records using the given configuration
193     **/
194    public static String serialize(Set<Id> ids, SerializeConfig strategy)
195    {            
196        // Validate parameters
197        if(ids==null || ids.size()==0)
198            throw new SerializerException('List of Ids cannot be null or empty.');
199            
200        // Container to bundle record sets into 
201        RecordsBundle recordsToBundle = new RecordsBundle();
202        recordsToBundle.recordSetBundles = new List<RecordSetBundle>();        
203        recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType = new Map<String, RecordSetBundle>();
204        
205        // Begin recursive serialize from given records through to related records
206        Schema.SObjectType sObjectType = new List<Id>(ids)[0].getSObjectType();
207        serialize(ids, sObjectType, null, strategy, 0, 0, recordsToBundle);
208                
209        // Serialise the records bundle container        
210        return JSON.serialize(recordsToBundle);                 
211    }
212
213    /**
214     * Deserialize the given JSON record set bundle
215     **/
216    public static Set<Id> deserialize(String recordsBundleAsJSON)
217    {
218        return deserialize(recordsBundleAsJSON, null);
219    }
220        
221    /**
222     * Deserialize the given JSON record set bundle utilising the given callback
223     **/
224    public static Set<Id> deserialize(String recordsBundleAsJSON, IDeserializeCallback callback)
225    {
226        // Desearialise the records bundle
227        RecordsBundle recordsBundle = (RecordsBundle) 
228            JSON.deserialize(recordsBundleAsJSON, GLBL_SobjectDataLoader.RecordsBundle.class);
229        
230        // Map to track original ID's against the new SObject record instances being inserted
231        Map<Id, SObject> recordsByOriginalId = new Map<Id, SObject>();
232        
233        // Record set bundles are already ordered in dependency order due to serialisation approach
234        Map<String, Schema.SObjectType> sObjectsByType = Schema.getGlobalDescribe();
235        for(RecordSetBundle recordSetBundle : recordsBundle.recordSetBundles)
236        {
237            // Determine lookup / relationship fields to update prior to inserting these records
238            Schema.SObjectType sObjectType = sObjectsByType.get(recordSetBundle.ObjectType);
239            Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectType.getDescribe().fields.getMap();
240            List<Schema.SObjectField> relationshipsFields = new List<Schema.SObjectField>();
241            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFields.values())
242                if(sObjectField.getDescribe().getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference) 
243                    relationshipsFields.add(sObjectField);
244                                    
245            // Prepare records for insert
246            List<SObject> recordsToInsert = new List<SObject>();
247            List<UnresolvedReferences> unresolvedReferencesByRecord = new List<UnresolvedReferences>(); 
248            for(SObject orignalRecord : recordSetBundle.Records)
249            {
250                // Clone the deserialised SObject to remove the original Id prior to inserting it
251                SObject newRecord = orignalRecord.clone();
252                recordsToInsert.add(newRecord);
253                // Map the new cloned record to its old Id (once inserted this can be used to obtain the new id)
254                recordsByOriginalId.put(orignalRecord.Id, newRecord);
255                // Update foreign key references / lookups / master-detail relationships
256                if(relationshipsFields.size()>0)
257                {
258                    Set<Schema.SObjectField> unresolvedFieldReferences = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>(); 
259                    for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : relationshipsFields)
260                    {                            
261                        // Obtained original related record Id and search map over new records by old Ids
262                        Id oldRelatedRecordId = (Id) orignalRecord.get(sObjectField);
263                        SObject newRelatedRecord = recordsByOriginalId.get(oldRelatedRecordId);
264                        if(newRelatedRecord!=null)
265                            newRecord.put(sObjectField, newRelatedRecord.Id);
266                        else
267                            unresolvedFieldReferences.add(sObjectField);
268                    }
269                    // Retain a list of records with unresolved references
270                    if(unresolvedFieldReferences.size()>0)
271                    {
272                        UnresolvedReferences unresolvedReferences = new UnresolvedReferences();
273                        unresolvedReferences.Record = newRecord;
274                        unresolvedReferences.References = unresolvedFieldReferences;
275                        unresolvedReferencesByRecord.add(unresolvedReferences);
276                    }    
277                }
278            }            
279            
280            // Let the caller attempt to resolve any references the above could not
281            if(callback!=null && unresolvedReferencesByRecord.size()>0)
282                callback.unresolvedReferences(sObjectType, unresolvedReferencesByRecord);
283            
284            if(callback!=null)
285                callback.cloneMapHandler(recordsByOriginalId);
286
287            // Insert cloned deserialised records
288            recordSetBundle.Records = recordsToInsert;
289            insert recordSetBundle.Records;
290        }
291        
292        // Return Id list from the first bundle set
293        return new Map<Id, SObject>(recordsBundle.recordSetBundles[0].Records).keySet();
294    }
295            
296    private static void serialize(Set<ID> ids, Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, Schema.SObjectField queryByIdField, SerializeConfig config, Integer lookupDepth, Integer childDepth, RecordsBundle recordsToBundle)
297    {        
298        // Config?
299        if(config==null)
300            throw new SerializerException('Must pass a valid SerializeConfig instance.');
301        // Stop infinite recursion
302        if(lookupDepth > 3 || childDepth > 3) // TODO: Make max depth configurable
303            return;
304            
305        // Describe object and determine fields to serialize
306        Schema.DescribeSObjectResult sObjectDesc = sObjectType.getDescribe();
307        Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectDesc.fields.getMap();
308        List<Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFieldsToSerialize = listFieldsToSerialize(sObjectFields, config);
309        
310        // Query records to serialize
311        String fieldList = null;
312        for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFieldsToSerialize)
313            fieldList = fieldList == null ? sObjectField.getDescribe().getName() : fieldList + ',' + sObjectField.getDescribe().getName();
314        String query = String.format('select {0} from {1} where {2} in :ids order by {2}', 
315            new List<String> { fieldList, sObjectDesc.getName(), queryByIdField == null ? 'id' : queryByIdField.getDescribe().getName(), 'Name' });
316        Map<Id, SObject> recordsToSerializeById = new Map<Id, SObject>(Database.query(query));
317        if(recordsToSerializeById.size()==0)
318            return;
319
320        // Any lookup relationships to folow?
321        Set<Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFollowRelationships = config.followRelationships.clone();
322        sObjectFollowRelationships.retainAll(sObjectFields.values());
323        if(sObjectFollowRelationships.size()>0)
324        {                
325            // Build list of ID's for each related record
326            Map<Schema.DescribeFieldResult, Set<Id>> relationshipsByField = new Map<Schema.DescribeFieldResult, Set<Id>>(); 
327            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFollowRelationships)
328                relationShipsByField.put(sObjectField.getDescribe(), new Set<Id>() );            
329            for(SObject recordToSerialize : recordsToSerializeById.values())
330            {
331                for(Schema.DescribeFieldResult relationshipField : relationshipsByField.keySet())
332                {
333                    Id relatedId = (Id) recordToSerialize.get(relationshipField.getSObjectField());
334                    if(relatedId!=null)
335                        relationshipsByField.get(relationshipField).add(relatedId);
336                }
337            }
338            // Serialise related records
339            for(Schema.DescribeFieldResult relationshipField : relationshipsByField.keySet())
340            {
341                Set<Id> relatedRecordIds = relationshipsByField.get(relationshipField);
342                if(relatedRecordIds.size()>0)
343                    serialize(relatedRecordIds, relationshipField.getReferenceTo()[0], null, config, lookupDepth+1, childDepth, recordsToBundle);                    
344            }
345        }
346                    
347        // Add records to applicable record set bundle
348        RecordSetBundle recordSetBundle = recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType.get(sObjectDesc.getName());
349        if(recordSetBundle!=null)
350        {
351            recordSetBundle.Records.addAll(recordsToSerializeById.values());
352        }
353        else if(recordSetBundle==null)
354        {
355            recordSetBundle = new RecordSetBundle();
356            recordSetBundle.ObjectType = sObjectDesc.getName();
357            recordSetBundle.Records = recordsToSerializeById.values();
358            recordsToBundle.recordSetBundles.add(recordSetBundle);
359            recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType.put(recordSetBundle.ObjectType, recordSetBundle);
360        }
361                
362        // Any child relationships to follow?
363        List<Schema.ChildRelationship> childRelationships = sObjectDesc.getChildRelationships();
364        for(Schema.ChildRelationship childRelationship : childRelationships)
365        { 
366            // Is this a child relationship we have been asked to follow?
367            Schema.SObjectType childSObjectType = childRelationship.getChildSObject();
368            if(config.followChildRelationships.contains(childRelationship.getField()))
369                serialize(recordsToSerializeById.keySet(), childSObjectType, childRelationship.getField(), config, lookupDepth, childDepth+1, recordsToBundle);
370        }
371    }
372    
373    private static List<Schema.SObjectField> listFieldsToSerialize(Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields, SerializeConfig config)
374    {
375        // Filter fields to serialise
376        List<Schema.SObjectField> serializeFields = new List<Schema.SObjectField>(); 
377        List<String> fieldNames = new List<String>(sObjectFields.keySet());
378        fieldNames.sort();
379        for(String fieldName : fieldNames)
380        {
381            // Skip fields indicated in config
382            Schema.SObjectField sObjectField = sObjectFields.get(fieldName);
383            if(config.omitFields!=null && config.omitFields.contains(sObjectField))
384                continue;
385            // Skip read only fields, such as auto numbers and formula fields
386            Schema.DescribeFieldResult sObjectFieldDescribe = sObjectField.getDescribe();
387            if(sObjectFieldDescribe.isAutoNumber() ||
388               sObjectFieldDescribe.isCalculated())
389               continue;    
390            // Skip lookup fields not in either of the follow lists
391            if(sObjectFieldDescribe.getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference)
392                if(!(config.followRelationships.contains(sObjectField) ||
393                     config.followChildRelationships.contains(sObjectField) ||
394                     config.followMasterRelationships.contains(sObjectField)))
395                   continue;
396            // Serialize this field..                        
397            serializeFields.add(sObjectField);
398        }            
399        return serializeFields;    
400    }

GLBL_TriggerHandler.cls

(93% covered)

Show Coverage
1/**
2 * @author Joseph Ferraro
3 *
4 * Generic handler for Trigger actions, example:
5 *
6 *   trigger MyTriggerName on MyObjectName (before insert, before update, after update) {
7 *       new GLBL_TriggerHandler()
8 *           .bind(GLBL_TriggerHandler.Evt.beforeinsert, new ClassThatImplementsGLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface())
9 *           .bind(GLBL_TriggerHandler.Evt.beforeupdate, new ClassThatImplementsGLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface())
10 *           .manage();
11 *   }
12 *
13 */
14
15public class GLBL_TriggerHandler 
16{
17    /**
18     *   Enum representing each of before/after CRUD events on Sobjects
19     */
20    public enum Evt 
21    {
22        afterdelete, afterinsert, afterundelete,
23        afterupdate, beforedelete, beforeinsert, beforeupdate   
24    }
25
26    /*
27     *   Simplistic handler to implement on any of the event. It doesn't require or enforces any pattern except the
28     *   method name to be "handle()".
29     */
30    public interface HandlerInterface
31    {
32        void handle();          
33    } 
34
35    // Internal mapping of handlers
36    map<String, list<HandlerInterface>> eventHandlerMapping = new map<String, list<HandlerInterface>>();
37
38    /**
39     *   Core API to bind handlers with events
40     */
41    public GLBL_TriggerHandler bind(Evt event, HandlerInterface eh)
42    {
43        list<HandlerInterface> handlers = eventHandlerMapping.get(event.name());
44        if (handlers == null) 
45        {
46            handlers = new list<HandlerInterface>();
47            eventHandlerMapping.put(event.name(), handlers);
48        }
49        handlers.add(eh);
50        return this;
51    }
52
53    /**
54     *   Invokes correct handlers as per the context of trigger and available registered handlers
55     */
56    public void manage()
57    {
58        Evt ev = null;
59        if(trigger.isInsert && trigger.isBefore)
60        {
61            ev = Evt.beforeinsert;
62        }
63        else if(trigger.isInsert && trigger.isAfter)
64        {
65            ev = Evt.afterinsert;
66        }
67        else if(trigger.isUpdate && trigger.isBefore)
68        {
69            ev = Evt.beforeupdate;
70        }
71        else if(trigger.isUpdate && trigger.isAfter)
72        {
73            ev = Evt.afterupdate;
74        }
75        else if(trigger.isDelete && trigger.isBefore)
76        {
77            ev = Evt.beforedelete;
78        }
79        else if(trigger.isDelete && trigger.isAfter)
80        {
81            ev = Evt.afterdelete;
82        }
83        else if(trigger.isundelete)
84        {
85            ev = Evt.afterundelete;             
86        }
87        
88        list<HandlerInterface> handlers = eventHandlerMapping.get(ev.name());
89        
90        if (handlers != null && ! handlers.isEmpty()) 
91        {
92            for (HandlerInterface h : handlers) 
93            {
94                h.handle();
95            }
96        }
97    }
98}

57            }

60    }
61
62    public override PageReference save() {
63        if (meeting.Agenda_Status_MERC__c == 'Final' && !this.confirmAgendaChange) {
64            tz.convertDateTimes(getSobjects(children), true, meeting.Meeting_Time_Zone_MERC__c); //sets date/times based on UTC, stamps static text with "user-friendly" date/time values
65            this.hasError = true;
66            this.pageMessage = 'Please confirm the change to the final agenda';
67            return null;
68        }
69        this.confirmAgendaChange = false;
70        tz.convertDateTimes(getSobjects(children), true, meeting.Meeting_Time_Zone_MERC__c); //sets date/times based on UTC, stamps static text with "user-friendly" date/time values
71        //return super.save();
72        try {
73            List<Sobject> childrenToInsert = new List<Sobject>();
74            List<Sobject> childrenToUpdate = new List<Sobject>();
75            List<GenericSobjectWrapper> childrenList;
76            if (recordTypeDeveloperNameParam != null) {
77                childrenList = childrenMap.get(recordTypeDeveloperNameParam);
78            } else {

80            }

87                    sow.so.put(parentFieldAPIName, parentId);
88                    childrenToInsert.add(sow.so);    
89                }
90            }
91            insert childrenToInsert;
92            update childrenToUpdate;
93            this.hasError = false;
94            this.pageMessage = 'Meeting Agenda updated successfully!';
95            if (MERC_Util.getUrlParam('notify') == '1') {
96                ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.CONFIRM, MERC_Util.getUrlParam('msg')));
97                return null;
98            } else if (MERC_Util.getUrlParam('retNull') == '1') {
99                return null;
100            } else {
101                return new PageReference('/'+parentId);
102            }
103        } catch (Exception e) {

105            this.hasError = true;
106            //ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.ERROR, e.getMessage()));
107            ApexPages.addMessages(e); //doesn't show ugly error text
108            return null;
109        }

39        if (budget.Master_Budget_MERC__c == null)
40            newBudget.Master_Budget_MERC__c = budget.Id;

49        //newBudget.Meeting_MERC__c = budget.Meeting_MERC__c; //we don't set this here anymore bc budget is now detail of meeting, which means it's set in the clone process

71                previousBudgetRev.Status_MERC__c = 'Archived';

97        public void cloneMapHandler(Map<ID, Sobject> cloneMap) {

99                String objectAPIName = recordId.getSObjectType().getDescribe().getName();

106                    newObject.put('Previous_Budget_Line_Item_Version_MERC__c', recordId);
107                    if (newObject.get('Version_Number_MERC__c') == null)
108                        newObject.put('Version_Number_MERC__c', 1);
109                    newObject.put('Version_Number_MERC__c', (Double)newObject.get('Version_Number_MERC__c')+1);
110                }
111            }
112        }

MERC_ConsultingProjectCapCalculator.cls

1/**
2 * @author Joseph Ferraro
3 *
4 * Trigger handler that calculates Consulting_Project_Paid_CAP_MERC__c on Account based on an Account's participation in Consulting projects for the year

6
7public with sharing class MERC_ConsultingProjectCapCalculator implements GLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface {
8    
9    Schema.SobjectType triggeredSobjectType;
10
11    public MERC_ConsultingProjectCapCalculator(Schema.SobjectType sobjectType) {
12        this.triggeredSobjectType = sObjectType;
13    }
14
15    public void handle() {
16        if (Trigger.isUpdate || Trigger.isUndelete) {
17            execute(Trigger.new);
18           } else if (Trigger.isDelete) {
19               execute(Trigger.old);
20           }
21    }
22
23    void execute(List<Sobject> sobjects) {
24        List<Invoice_MERC__c> invoices;
25        if (this.triggeredSobjectType == Invoice_MERC__c.sObjectType) {
26            invoices = (List<Invoice_MERC__c>)sobjects;
27        } else if (this.triggeredSobjectType == Invoice_Line_Item_MERC__c.sObjectType) {
28            Set<Id> invoiceIds = new Set<Id>();
29            for (Sobject lineItem : sobjects) {
30                invoiceIds.add((Id)lineItem.get('Invoice_MERC__c'));
31            }
32            invoices = [SELECT ID, Meeting_Participant_Account_Id_MERC__c FROM Invoice_MERC__c WHERE ID in :invoiceIds];
33        }
34
35        if (invoices.size() == 0) return;
36
37        Set<Id> meetingParticipantIds = new Set<Id>();
38        Set<Id> accountIds = new Set<Id>();
39
40        for (Invoice_MERC__c i : invoices)
41            accountIds.add(i.Meeting_Participant_Account_Id_MERC__c);
42
43        System.debug('>>>> '+accountIds);
44
45        List<AggregateResult> results = [SELECT 
46                                            Meeting_Participant_MERC__r.Account_MERC__c, 
47                                            Sum(Consulting_Project_Amount_excl_VAT_MERC__c) lre0 
48                                                FROM Invoice_MERC__c 
49                                                    WHERE 
50                                                        Meeting_Participant_MERC__r.Account_MERC__c IN :accountIds AND 
51                                                        Invoice_Date_MERC__c = THIS_YEAR 
52                                                            GROUP BY Meeting_Participant_MERC__r.Account_MERC__c];
53
54        System.debug('>>>> '+results);
55
56        List<Account> accounts = new List<Account>();
57
58        for (AggregateResult res : results){
59            System.debug('========== '+res);
60            Id masterRecId = (Id)res.get('Account_MERC__c');
61            if (masterRecId == null) {
62                System.debug(Logginglevel.WARN, 'No master record found for ID :' + masterRecId);
63                continue;
64            }
65            Object aggregatedDetailVal = res.get('lre0');
66            Account a = new Account();
67            a.Id = masterRecId;
68            a.Consulting_Project_Paid_CAP_MERC__c = (Decimal)aggregatedDetailVal;
69            accounts.add(a);            
70        }
71
72        update accounts;
73    }

30                d.RecordTypeId = objectTypeToContentRecordId.get('Invoice_MERC');
31            } else if (d.Meeting_MERC__c != null) {

35            } else if (d.Meeting_Participant_MERC__c != null) {

7 * -we're also reloading MP status when their status updates to show real-time TOV numbers. if this isn't necessary,

10public with sharing class MERC_DailyAttendanceController {

21
22    //make sure every meeting participant has a tov record for every meeting day
23    //todo move to trigger
24    public PageReference upsertMissingTovRecords() {
25        try {
26            List<Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c> tovsToUpsert = new List<Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c>();
27            
28            for (Meeting_Day_MERC__c day : [SELECT ID, (SELECT ID, Meeting_Participant_MERC__c FROM Daily_Attendance_TOV__r) FROM Meeting_Day_MERC__c WHERE Meeting_MERC__c = :meeting.Id]) {
29                Set<Id> participantIdsWithTovsForThisDay = new Set<Id>();
30                for (Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c tov : day.Daily_Attendance_TOV__r) {
31                    participantIdsWithTovsForThisDay.add(tov.Meeting_Participant_MERC__c);
32                }
33                for (Id participantId : participantIds) {
34                    if (!participantIdsWithTovsForThisDay.contains(participantId)) {
35                         Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c tovRecord = new Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c();
36                        tovRecord.Meeting_Participant_MERC__c = participantId;
37                        tovRecord.Meeting_Day_MERC__c = day.Id;
38                        tovRecord.External_ID_MERC__c = participantId+'_'+day.Id;
39                        tovsToUpsert.add(tovRecord);    
40                    }
41                }
42            }
43            if (tovsToUpsert.size() > 0) {
44                upsert tovsToUpsert External_ID_MERC__c;
45                PageReference p = Page.MERC_DailyAttendance;
46                p.getParameters().put('id', meeting.Id);
47                p.setRedirect(true);
48                return p;
49            }
50            return null;
51        } catch (Exception e) {
52            this.hasError = true;
53            ApexPages.addMessages(e); //doesn't show ugly error text
54            return null;
55        }
56    }
57
58    Set<Id> participantIds {
59        get {
60            if (participantIds == null) {
61                participantIds = new Set<Id>();
62                Id employeeRecordTypeId = [SELECT ID FROM RecordType WHERE SobjectType = 'Account' and DeveloperName = 'Employee_GLBL'].ID;
63                List<String> excludedStatuses = new List<String>{ 'Pending Approval', 'Declined', 'Interested in Meeting', 'Cancelled' };
64                for (Meeting_Participant_MERC__c p : [SELECT ID FROM 
65                                                                    Meeting_Participant_MERC__c 
66                                                                        WHERE 
67                                                                            Meeting_MERC__c = :meeting.Id AND
68                                                                            Account_MERC__r.RecordTypeId != :employeeRecordTypeId AND
69                                                                            Status_MERC__c NOT IN :excludedStatuses
70                                                    ]) {
71                    participantIds.add(p.Id);
72                }
73            }
74            return participantIds;
75        }
76        private set;
77    }

79    void validate() {
80        if (meetingDays.size() == 0) {
81            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Error, 'Please add Meeting Days to this Meeting.'));
82            this.hasError = true;
83        }
84        if (!this.hasError)
85            this.selectedMeetingDayId = meetingDays.get(0).Id;
86        if (participants.size() == 0) {
87            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Error, 'Only those Meeting Participants that are allocated to attend (e.g. Not Declined, Interested in Meeting, Rejected, Cancelled or Pending Approval) will appear in this list.  Please ensure Meeting Participants have been added to the Meeting and all Meeting Participants have the correct Status.'));
88            this.hasError = true;
89        }
90        if (!this.hasError) {
91            this.hasError = false;
92        }
93    }

178    public List<SelectOption> getMeetingDayOptions() {
179        List<SelectOption> options = new List<SelectOption>();
180        for (Meeting_Day_MERC__c m : meetingDays) {
181            if (m.Date_MERC__c != null) {
182                Datetime myDatetime = Datetime.newInstance(m.Date_MERC__c, Time.newInstance(12, 0, 0, 0));
183                String sFormattedDate = myDatetime.format('MMMM d,  yyyy');
184                options.add(new SelectOption((String)m.Id, m.Name + ' (' + sFormattedDate + ')'));
185            } else {
186                options.add(new SelectOption((String)m.Id, m.Name));
187            }
188        }
189        return options;
190    }

192    public List<ParticipantWrapper> participants {
193        get {

196                for (Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c tovRecord : [SELECT 
197                                                                    Id, Name, 
198                                                                    Meeting_Day_MERC__c, 
199                                                                    Meeting_Participant_MERC__c, 
200                                                                    Est_Food_Bev_ToV_MERC__c,
201                                                                    Est_Grnd_Transp_MERC__c,
202                                                                    Est_Reg_Amt_ToV_MERC__c,
203                                                                    Est_Hotel_ToV_MERC__c,
204                                                                    Status_MERC__c, External_ID_MERC__c, 
205                                                                    Meeting_Participant_Record_Type_MERC__c,
206                                                                    Meeting_Participant_Account_Name_MERC__c 
207                                                                        FROM Daily_Attendance_TOV_MERC__c 
208                                                                        WHERE Meeting_Day_MERC__c = :this.selectedMeetingDayId 
209                                                                        ORDER BY Meeting_Participant_Account_Name_MERC__c]) 
210                {
211                    participants.add(new ParticipantWrapper(tovRecord));
212                }
213            }
214            if (this.refreshParticipants)
215                this.refreshParticipants = false;
216
217            return participants;
218        }
219        set;
220    }

1/**
2 * @author Joseph Ferraro
3 *
4 * Service which notifies the Real-Time Integration listener of deletes
5 */
6
7public with sharing class MERC_DeleteNotifyService implements GLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface {
8    
9    public static Boolean skipCallout = false;
10
11    public void handle() {
12        List<Sobject> sobjects = Trigger.old;
13        String sobjectTypeAPIName = MERC_Util.getSobjectAPIName(sobjects.get(0));
14        String serializedSobjects = Json.serialize(sobjects); 
15        String sessionId = UserInfo.getSessionId();
16        //we need to send primitives because execute method is @future
17        if (!MERC_DeleteNotifyService.skipCallout)
18            MERC_DeleteNotifyService.execute(sobjectTypeAPIName, serializedSobjects, sessionId);
19    }
20
21    @Future(callout=true)
22    public static void execute(String sobjectType, String serializedSobjects, String sessionId) {
23        DeleteNotification notification = new DeleteNotification(sobjectType, serializedSobjects, sessionId);
24        String jsonstring = Json.serialize(notification); 
25        system.debug(jsonstring);
26
27        HttpRequest r = new HttpRequest();
28        r.setHeader('Content-type', 'text/json');
29        r.setEndpoint('http://ec2-54-227-9-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/rti-development/v1/genericDeleted'); //todo custom setting
30        r.setMethod('POST');
31        r.setBody(jsonstring);
32
33        Http h = new Http();
34        HttpResponse response = h.send(r);
35        system.debug(response.getBody());
36    }
37
38    public class DeleteNotification {
39        String notificationId;
40        String orgId;
41        String sessionId;
42        String sobjectTypeAPIName;
43        String instanceUrl;
44        List<Sobject> records;
45        public DeleteNotification(String sobjectType, String serializedSobjects, String sessionId) {
46            this.notificationId = MERC_Util.generateRandomString(30);
47            this.records = (List<Sobject>)JSON.deserialize(serializedSobjects, List<Sobject>.class); //we need to deserialize here to ensure "records" is not double encoded before we send to listener
48            this.sobjectTypeAPIName = sobjectType;
49            this.orgId = UserInfo.getOrganizationId();
50            this.sessionId = sessionId;
51            this.instanceUrl = 'https://' + System.URL.getSalesforceBaseURL().getHost();
52        }
53    }
54}

144    String getEnvelope(List<RequiredSigner> requiredSigners, Boolean isDraft) {
145        //set up documents to be signed
146        Document d = new Document();
147        d.name = 'contract.pdf';
148        d.documentId = '1';
149        d.order = '1';
150        List<Document> docs = new List<Document>();
151        docs.add(d);
152
153        //set location(s) for Lilly signature
154        List<SignHereTab> lillySignHereTabs = new List<SignHereTab> { 
155            new SignHereTab(this.lillySignatureAnchorString, '0', '10', '1') 
156        };
157        Tab lillyTab = new Tab();
158        lillyTab.signHereTabs = lillySignHereTabs;
159
160        //set location(s) for HCP signature
161        List<SignHereTab> hcpSignHereTabs = new List<SignHereTab>{ 
162            new SignHereTab(this.hcpSignatureAnchorString, '0', '10', '2') 
163        };
164        Tab hcpTab = new Tab();
165        hcpTab.signHereTabs = hcpSignHereTabs;
166
167       
168        
169        List<Signer> signers = new List<Signer>();
170        
171        for (RequiredSigner rs : requiredSigners) {
172            //add signers
173            Signer s = new Signer(rs.acc.PersonEmail, rs.acc.Name, String.valueOf(rs.order), String.valueOf(rs.order));
174            if (rs.isLilly) {
175                if (!isDraft) 
176                    s.tabs = lillyTab;
177            } else {
178                if (!isDraft) 
179                    s.tabs = hcpTab;
180            }
181            signers.add(s);
182        }
183
184        Recipient r = new Recipient();
185        r.signers = signers;
186
187        Envelope e = new Envelope();
188        e.status = (isDraft) ? 'created' : 'sent';
189        e.emailBlurb = 'hi';
190        e.emailSubject = 'hi there';
191        e.documents = docs;
192        e.recipients = r;
193
194        String envelopeJson = JSON.serializePretty(e);
195        //system.debug(envelopeJson);
196        return envelopeJson;
197    }

39                                            Meeting_MERC__c in :meetingIdsToProcess];

41            } else {

MERC_HcpCapLimitCalculator.cls

(57% covered)

Show Coverage
1/**
2 * @author Joseph Ferraro
3 *
4 * Responsible for calculating annual cap limit for HCP based on CAP_Settings_MERC__c Custom Setting data
5 */
6
7
8public with sharing class MERC_HcpCapLimitCalculator implements GLBL_TriggerHandler.HandlerInterface {
9
10    public void handle() {
11        if (Trigger.isInsert || Trigger.isUpdate ) {
12            execute(Trigger.new);
13           }
14    }
15
16    void execute(List<Sobject> sobjects) {
17        List<Account> accs = (List<Account>)sobjects;
18        List<Account> accountsToProcess = new List<Account>();
19        Set<String> countries = new Set<String>();
20        for (Account a : accs) {
21            if (Trigger.isInsert) {
22                if (a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c != null)
23                    countries.add(a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c);
24                    accountsToProcess.add(a);
25            } else if (Trigger.isUpdate) {
26                if ((String)Trigger.oldMap.get(a.Id).get('Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c') != a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c) {
27                    if (a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c != null) {
28                        countries.add(a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c);
29                        accountsToProcess.add(a);
30                    } else {
31                        a.Annual_CAP_Limit_MERC__c = null;
32                    }
33                }
34            }
35        }
36
37        String currentYear = String.valueOf(Date.today().year());
38        Map<String, List<CAP_Settings_MERC__c>> capMap = new Map<String, List<CAP_Settings_MERC__c>>();
39        for (CAP_Settings_MERC__c capSetting : [SELECT 
40                                                    Annual_Amount_MERC__c, 
41                                                    Year_MERC__c,
42                                                    Country_Code_MERC__c, 
43                                                    Currency_Code_MERC__c
44                                                        FROM CAP_Settings_MERC__c 
45                                                            WHERE Country_Code_MERC__c in :countries AND Year_MERC__c = :currentYear]) {
46            if (capMap.containsKey(capSetting.Country_Code_MERC__c)) {
47                List<CAP_Settings_MERC__c> capList = capMap.get(capSetting.Country_Code_MERC__c);
48                capList.add(capSetting);
49                capMap.put(capSetting.Country_Code_MERC__c, capList);
50            } else {
51                List<CAP_Settings_MERC__c> capList = new List<CAP_Settings_MERC__c>{capSetting};
52                capMap.put(capSetting.Country_Code_MERC__c, capList);
53            }
54        }
55
56        for (Account a : accountsToProcess) {
57            String accountCountry = a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c;
58            List<CAP_Settings_MERC__c> capSettings = capMap.get(a.Country_of_Residence_GLBL__c);
59            
60            if (capSettings != null) {
61                for (CAP_Settings_MERC__c capSetting : capSettings) {
62                    if (capSetting.Country_Code_MERC__c == accountCountry) {
63                        a.Annual_CAP_Limit_MERC__c = capSetting.Annual_Amount_MERC__c;
64                        break;
65                    }
66                }
67            }
68        }
69    }
70}

67                Schema.DescribeSObjectResult objectDescribe = this.sObjectType.getDescribe();
68                String objectNameString = objectDescribe.getName();
69
70                Map<String, Schema.SObjectType> globalDescription = Schema.getGlobalDescribe();  
71                Schema.sObjectType sObjType = globalDescription.get(objectNameString); 
72                Schema.DescribeSObjectResult r1 = sObjType.getDescribe();  
73                fieldListMap = r1.fields.getMap();  
74                return fieldListMap;
75            } else {
76                return null;
77            }    
78        }
79        set;
80    }
81
82    Map<Id, Sobject> parentMap {
83        get {
84            if (parentMap == null && this.parentSobjectType != null) {
85                parentMap = new Map<Id, Sobject>();
86                Set<Id> parentObjectIds = new Set<Id>();
87                for (SObject s : this.sobjects)
88                    parentObjectIds.add((Id)s.get(this.parentLookupField.getName()));
89                for (Sobject s : Database.query('SELECT Id, '+this.lockedFieldAPIName+' FROM '+this.parentSobjectType.getDescribe().getName()+' Where Id in :parentObjectIds'))
90                    parentMap.put((Id)s.get('Id'), s);
91            } 
92            return parentMap;
93        }
94        set;
95    }
96
97    Boolean isSystemAdmin {
98        get {
99            //return [SELECT Profile.Name FROM User WHERE ID = :UserInfo.getUserId()].Profile.Name == 'System Administrator';
100            return false;
101        }
102    }
103
104    String errorMessage {
105        get {
106            try {
107                if (this.parentSobjectType != null) {
108                    return sObjectToErrorMessage.get(this.parentSobjectType);
109                } else {
110                    return sObjectToErrorMessage.get(this.sObjectType);
111                }
112            } catch(Exception e) {
113                if (this.parentSobjectType != null) {
114                    return 'Operation failed: Parent record is locked';
115                } else {
116                    return 'Operation failed: Record is locked';
117                }
118            }
119        }
120    }
121
122    public void handle() {
123        if (!MERC_LockedRecordHandler.overrideLockCheck) {
124            if (Trigger.isBefore) {
125                if (Trigger.isInsert || Trigger.isUpdate || Trigger.isUndelete) {
126                    this.sobjects = Trigger.new;
127                    execute();
128                } else if (Trigger.isDelete) {
129                    this.sobjects = Trigger.old;
130                    execute();
131                }
132            }
133        }
134    }
135
136    Boolean getIsLockedFromEditing(Sobject s) {
137        if (this.sObjectIsChild) {
138            Id parentId = (Id)s.get(this.parentLookupField.getName());
139            if (parentId == null) {
140                return false;
141            } else {
142                Sobject parent = this.parentMap.get(parentId);
143                return (Boolean)parent.get(this.lockedFieldAPIName) && !isSystemAdmin;
144            }
145        } else {
146            return (Boolean)s.get(this.lockedFieldAPIName) && !isSystemAdmin;
147        }
148    }
149
150    public void execute() {
151        
152        for (SObject s : this.sobjects) {
153            Id recordId = (Id)s.get('Id');
154            Boolean isLocked = getIsLockedFromEditing(s);
155            
156            if (!this.sObjectIsChild) {
157                if (Trigger.isUpdate) {
158                    Boolean oldLockValue = (Boolean)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(this.lockedFieldAPIName);
159                    Boolean newLockValue = (Boolean)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(this.lockedFieldAPIName);
160                    if (oldLockValue != newLockValue)
161                        continue; //user is unlocking/locking the record
162                }
163            }
164
165
166            if (Trigger.isUpdate && this.exemptFields != null) {
167                Boolean isUpdateOK = true; //this is set to false if user attempts to edit non-exempt field
168                String fieldName;
169                String fieldType;
170                Boolean isCalculated; //whether this is a formula field
171                
172                for (Schema.SObjectField field : fieldListMap.values()) {
173
174                    Schema.DescribeFieldResult fieldDescribe = field.getDescribe(); 
175                    fieldName = String.valueOf(fieldDescribe.getName());
176                    fieldType = String.valueOf(fieldDescribe.getSoaptype());
177                    isCalculated = Boolean.valueOf(fieldDescribe.isCalculated());
178
179                    if (isCalculated) continue; //we can't control this, so we let it go
180
181                    if (fieldName != this.lockedFieldAPIName){
182                        if (fieldType == 'DOUBLE') {
183                            Double oldFieldValue = (Double)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
184                            Double newFieldValue = (Double)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
185                            if (oldFieldValue != newFieldValue && !exemptFields.contains(fieldName)) {
186                                isUpdateOK = false;
187                                break;
188                            }
189                        } else if (fieldType == 'STRING') {
190                            String oldFieldValue = (String)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
191                            String newFieldValue = (String)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
192                            if (oldFieldValue != newFieldValue && !exemptFields.contains(fieldName)) {
193                                isUpdateOK = false;
194                                break;
195                            }
196                        } else if (fieldType == 'DATE') {
197                            Date oldFieldValue = (Date)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
198                            Date newFieldValue = (Date)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
199                            if (oldFieldValue != newFieldValue && !exemptFields.contains(fieldName)) {
200                                isUpdateOK = false;
201                                break;
202                            }
203                        } else if (fieldType == 'BOOLEAN') {
204                            Boolean oldFieldValue = (Boolean)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
205                            Boolean newFieldValue = (Boolean)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
206                            if (oldFieldValue != newFieldValue && !exemptFields.contains(fieldName)) {
207                                isUpdateOK = false;
208                                break;
209                            }
210                        } else if (fieldType == 'DATETIME') {
211                            DateTime oldFieldValue = (DateTime)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
212                            DateTime newFieldValue = (DateTime)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
213                            if (oldFieldValue != newFieldValue && !exemptFields.contains(fieldName)) {
214                                isUpdateOK = false;
215                                break;
216                            }
217                        } else if (fieldType == 'ID') {
218                            Id oldFieldValue = (Id)Trigger.oldmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
219                            Id newFieldValue = (Id)Trigger.newmap.get(recordId).get(fieldName);
220                            if (oldFieldValue != newFieldValue && !exemptFields.contains(fieldName)) {
221                                isUpdateOK = false;
222                                break;
223                            }
224                        }
225                    }                           
226                }
227                
228                system.debug('isupdateOK --> '+isUpdateOK);
229                system.debug('isLocked --> '+isLocked);
230
231                if (isLocked && !isUpdateOK) { //if it's locked and the update is not ok (they are not editing exempt fields) throw an error
232                    system.debug('--> record/parent locked and exempt field is not being updated, so no update allowed');
233                    s.addError(errorMessage);
234                } else if (isUpdateOK) {
235                    system.debug('--> update is ok because only exempt fields are being updated');
236                    MERC_LockedRecordHandler.overrideLockCheck = true;
237                }                    
238            } else {
239                if (isLocked)
240                    s.addError(errorMessage);
241            }
242        }
243    }
244}

36                if (tov.Status_MERC__c == 'Attended') {
37                    numberOfAttended++;
38                    break;
39                } else if (tov.Status_MERC__c == 'No Show') {

41                }
42            }

47            }

53    public ContentVersion contractContentVersion {

81    public PageReference requestSignature() {
82        Blob pdfBlob = [Select VersionData From ContentVersion Where Id = :contractContentVersion.Id].VersionData;
83        String pdfBytes = EncodingUtil.base64Encode(pdfBlob);
84
85        Account lillySigner = [Select Id, Name, PersonEmail From Account Where Id = :this.contract.Lilly_Internal_Signee_MERC__c];
86        Account hcpSigner = [Select Id, Name, PersonEmail From Account Where Id = :this.contract.Account_MERC__c];
87
88        List<MERC_DocusignService.RequiredSigner> signers = new List<MERC_DocusignService.RequiredSigner>();
89        
90        MERC_DocusignService.RequiredSigner s1 = new MERC_DocusignService.RequiredSigner();
91        s1.acc = lillySigner;
92        s1.isLilly = true;
93        s1.order = 1;
94        signers.add(s1);
95
96        MERC_DocusignService.RequiredSigner s2 = new MERC_DocusignService.RequiredSigner();
97        s2.acc = hcpSigner;
98        s2.isLilly = false;
99        s2.order = 2;
100        signers.add(s2);
101
102        MERC_DocusignService d = new MERC_DocusignService();
103        MERC_DocusignService.EnvelopeResponse r = d.requestSignature(signers, pdfBytes);
104        if (r.errorCode != null) {
105            if (r.errorCode == 'ANCHOR_TAB_STRING_NOT_FOUND') {
106                //get tag and send url
107                String returnUrl = 'https://' + System.URL.getSalesforceBaseUrl().getHost().remove('-api' ) + '/apex/MERC_RequestHCPSignature?docusignTasStatus=1&id='+this.contract.Id;
108                MERC_DocusignService.EnvelopeResponse r2 = d.requestSignature(signers, pdfBytes, True); //send as draft mode
109                MERC_DocusignService.TagAndSendResponse tasResponse = d.getTagAndSendUrl(r2, returnUrl); //get tas url
110                stampEnvelopeId(this.contract.Id, r2.envelopeId);
111                //redirect to tag and send url                
112                PageReference p = new PageReference(tasResponse.url);
113                return p;
114            } else {
115                //show error on vf page
116                ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Error, 'Docusign failed to send the contract for signature. Error code: '+r.errorCode));
117                this.isSent = false;
118                return null;
119            }
120        } else {
121            stampEnvelopeId(this.contract.Id, r.envelopeId);
122            this.isSent = true;
123            return null;
124        }
125    }

13    Map<Id, Set<Id>> getMeetingIdToTriggerUserIds(List<Team_Member_MERC__c> teamMembers) {
14        Map<Id, Set<Id>> meetingIdToUserIds = new Map<Id, Set<Id>>();
15        for (Team_Member_MERC__c m : teamMembers) {
16            if (meetingIdToUserIds.containsKey(m.Meeting_MERC__c)) {
17                Set<Id> existingSet = meetingIdToUserIds.get(m.Meeting_MERC__c);
18                existingSet.add(m.User_MERC__c);
19                meetingIdToUserIds.put(m.Meeting_MERC__c, existingSet);
20            } else {
21                Set<Id> newSet = new Set<Id>();
22                newSet.add(m.User_MERC__c);
23                meetingIdToUserIds.put(m.Meeting_MERC__c, newSet);
24            }
25        }
26        return meetingIdToUserIds;
27    }

29    public void execute(list<Sobject> sobjects) {        
30        Id mercuryUserRecordTypeId = [SELECT ID FROM RecordType WHERE DeveloperName = 'Mercury_User_MERC' AND SobjectType = 'Team_Member_MERC__c'].ID;
31        List<Team_Member_MERC__c> teamMembers = (List<Team_Member_MERC__c>)sobjects;
32        List<Team_Member_MERC__c> teamMembersToProcess = new List<Team_Member_MERC__c>();
33        Set<Id> meetingIds = new Set<Id>();
34        for (Team_Member_MERC__c tm : teamMembers) {
35            if (tm.RecordTypeId == mercuryUserRecordTypeId) {

37                meetingIds.add(tm.Meeting_MERC__c);
38            }
39        }
40        Map<Id, Meeting_MERC__c> meetingMap = new Map<ID, Meeting_MERC__c>([SELECT ID, OwnerId FROM Meeting_MERC__c WHERE ID in :meetingIds]);
41
42        if (Trigger.isInsert || Trigger.isUndelete) {
43            Map<Id, Set<Id>> meetingIdToNewUserIds = getMeetingIdToTriggerUserIds(teamMembersToProcess);
44            
45            List<Meeting_MERC__Share> shareRecordsToInsert = new List<Meeting_MERC__Share>();
46            for (Id meetingId : meetingIdToNewUserIds.keySet()) {

48                for (Id userId : userIdsToAddToShareTable) {
49                    if (userId != meetingMap.get(meetingId).OwnerId) {
